17 constituting a violation of this chapter or a rule adopted or order issued under this chapter,
18 the Commissioner may:
19 (1) Issue an order directing the person to cease and desist from engaging in the act,
20 practice, or course of business or to take other action necessary or appropriate to comply
21 with this chapter;
22 (2) Issue an order denying, suspending, revoking, or conditioning the exemptions for a
23 broker-dealer under subparagraph (b)(1)(D) or (b)(1)(F) of Code Section 10-5-30 or an
24 investment adviser under subparagraph (b)(1)(C) of Code Section 10-5-32; or
25 (3) Issue an order under Code Section 10-5-13; or
26 (4) Issue an order directing the person to return to investors, customers, or clients the
27 principal dollar amount of their securities purchases, as well as all moneys collected in
28 connection with those securities purchases, if the Commissioner determines that the
29 person has engaged or is engaging in an act, practice, or course of business constituting
30 a violation of Code Section 10-5-50, 10-5-51, or 10-5-54 or that the person has materially
31 aided or is materially aiding in an act, practice, or course of business constituting a
32 violation of Code Section 10-5-50, 10-5-51, or 10-5-54.
33 (b) An order under subsection (a) of this Code section is effective on the date of issuance.
34 Upon issuance of the order, the Commissioner shall promptly serve each person subject to
35 the order with a copy of the order and a notice that the order has been entered. The order
36 must shall include a statement whether the Commissioner will seek a civil penalty or costs
37 of the investigation, a statement of the reasons for the order, and notice that, within 30 days
38 after receipt of a request in a record from the person, the matter will be scheduled for a
39 hearing. If a person subject to the order does not request a hearing and none is ordered by
40 the Commissioner within 30 days after the date of service of the order, the order becomes
41 final as to that person by operation of law. If a hearing is requested or ordered, the
42 Commissioner, after notice of and opportunity for hearing to each person subject to the
43 order, may modify or vacate the order or extend it until final determination.
