44 (c) If a hearing is requested or ordered pursuant to subsection (b) of this Code section, a
45 hearing must shall be held pursuant to the provisions of Chapter 13 of Title 50, the 'Georgia
46 Administrative Procedure Act' and this chapter. A final order may shall not be issued
47 unless the Commissioner makes findings of fact and conclusions of law in a record. The
48 final order may make final, vacate, or modify the order issued under subsection (a) of this
49 Code section.
50 (d) In a final order under subsection (c) of this Code section, the Commissioner may
51 impose a civil penalty up to $50,000.00 for a single violation or up to $500,000.00 for more
52 than one violation.
53 (e) In a final order under subsection (c) of this Code section, the Commissioner may
54 charge the actual cost of an investigation or proceeding for a violation of this chapter or a
55 rule adopted or order issued under this chapter.
56 (f) If a petition for judicial review of a final order is not filed in accordance with Code
57 Section 10-5-78, the Commissioner may file a certified copy of the final order with the
58 clerk of a court of competent jurisdiction. The order so filed has the same effect as a
59 judgment of the court and may be recorded, enforced, or satisfied in the same manner as
60 a judgment of the court.
61 (g) If a person does not comply with an order under this Code section, the Commissioner
62 may petition a court of competent jurisdiction to enforce the order. The court may shall
63 not require the Commissioner to post a bond in an action or proceeding under this Code
64 section. If the court finds, after service and opportunity for hearing, that the person was
65 not in compliance with the order, the court may adjudge the person in civil contempt of the
66 order. The court may impose a further civil penalty against the person for contempt in an
67 amount not less than $5,000.00 but not greater than $50,000.00 for each violation and may
68 grant any other relief the court determines is just and proper in the circumstances."
